<?php 
switch($verse){
case 1:{?>The revelation of the Scripture is from Allah, the Mighty, the Wise.<?php break;}
case 2:{?>Lo! We have revealed the Scripture unto thee ( Muhammad ) with truth; so worship Allah, making religion pure for Him ( only ).<?php break;}
case 3:{?>Surely Pure religion is for Allah only. And those who choose protecting friends beside Him ( say ) : We worship them only that they may bring us near unto Allah. Lo! Allah will judge between them concerning that wherein they differ. Lo! Allah guideth not him who is a liar, an ingrate.<?php break;}
case 4:{?>If Allah had willed to choose a son, he could have chosen what he would of that which He hath created. Be He glorified! He is Allah, the One, the Absolute.<?php break;}
case 5:{?>He hath created the heavens and the earth with truth. He maketh night to succeed day, and He maketh day to succeed night, and He constraineth the sun and the moon to give service, each running on for an appointed term. Is not He the Mighty, the Forgiver?<?php break;}
case 6:{?>He created you from one being, then from that ( being ) He made its mate; and He hath provided for you of cattle eight kinds. He created you in the wombs of your mothers, creation after creation, in a threefold gloom. Such is Allah, your Lord. His is the Sovereignty. There is no God save Him. How then are ye turned away?<?php break;}
case 7:{?>If ye are thankless, yet Allah is Independent of you, though He is not pleased with thanklessness for His bondmen; and if ye are thankful He is pleased therewith for you. No laden soul will bear another ' s load. Then unto your Lord is your return; and He will tell you what ye used to do. Lo! He knoweth what is in the breasts ( of men ).<?php break;}
case 8:{?>And then some hurt toucheth man, he crieth unto his Lord, turning unto Him ( repentant ). Then, when He granteth him a boon from Him he forgetteth that for which he cried unto Him before, and setteth up rivals to Allah that he may beguile ( men ) from His way. Say ( O Muhammad, unto such an one ) : Take pleasure in thy disbelief a while. Lo! thou art of the owners of the Fire.<?php break;}
case 9:{?>Is he who payeth adoration in the watches of the night, prostrate and standing, bewaring of the Hereafter and hoping for the mercy of his Lord, ( to be accounted equal with a disbeliever )? Say ( unto them, O Muhammad ) : Are those who know equal with those who know not? But only men of understanding will pay heed.<?php break;}
case 10:{?>Say : O My bondmen who believe! Observe your duty to your Lord. For those who do good in this world there is good, and Allah ' s earth is spacious. Verily the steadfast will be paid their wages without stint.<?php break;}
case 11:{?>Say ( O Muhammad ) : Lo! I am commanded to worship Allah, making religion pure for Him ( only ).<?php break;}
case 12:{?>And I am commanded to be the first of those who surrender ( unto Him ).<?php break;}
case 13:{?>Say : Lo! if I should disobey my Lord, I fear the doom of a tremendous Day.<?php break;}
case 14:{?>Say : Allah I worship, making my religion pure for Him ( only ).<?php break;}
case 15:{?>Then worship what ye will beside Him. Say : The losers will be those who lose themselves and their housefolk on the Day of Resurrection. Ah, that will be the manifest loss!<?php break;}
case 16:{?>They have an awning of fire above them and beneath them a dais ( of fire ). With this doth Allah appall His bondmen. O My bondmen, therefor fear Me!<?php break;}
case 17:{?>And those who put away false gods lest they should worship them and turn to Allah in repentance, for them there are glad tidings. Therefor give good tidings ( O Muhammad ) to my bondmen<?php break;}
case 18:{?>Who hear advice and follow the best thereof. Such are those whom Allah guideth, and such are men of understanding.<?php break;}
case 19:{?>Is he on whom the word of doom is fulfilled ( to be helped ), and canst thou ( O Muhammad ) rescue him who is in the Fire?<?php break;}
case 20:{?>But those who keep their duty to their Lord, for them are lofty halls with lofty hails above them, built ( for them ), beneath which rivers flow. ( It is ) a promise of Allah. Allah faileth not His promise.<?php break;}
case 21:{?>Hast thou not seen how Allah hath sent down water from the sky and hath caused it to penetrate the earth as water springs, and afterward thereby produceth crops of divers hues; and afterward they wither and thou seest them turn yellow; then He maketh them chaff. Lo! herein verily is a reminder for men of understanding.<?php break;}
case 22:{?>Is he whose bosom Allah hath expanded for the Surrender ( unto Him ), so that he followeth a light from His Lord, ( as he who disbelieveth )? Then woe unto those whose hearts are hardened against remembrance of Allah. Such are in plain error.<?php break;}
case 23:{?>Allah hath ( now ) revealed the fairest of statements, a Scripture consistent, ( wherein promises of reward are ) paired ( with threats of punishment ), whereat doth creep the flesh of those who fear their Lord, so that their flesh and their hearts soften to Allah ' s reminder. Such is Allah ' s guidance, where with He guideth whom He will. And him whom Allah sendeth astray, for him there is no guide.<?php break;}
case 24:{?>Is he then, who will strike his face against the awful doom upon the Day of Resurrection ( as he who doeth right )? And it will be said unto the wrong doers : Taste what ye used to earn.<?php break;}
case 25:{?>Those before them denied, and so the doom came on them whence they knew not.<?php break;}
case 26:{?>Thus Allah made them taste humiliation in the life of the world, and verily the doom of the Hereafter will be greater if they did but know.<?php break;}
case 27:{?>And verily We have coined for mankind in this Quran all kinds of similitudes, that haply they may reflect;<?php break;}
case 28:{?>A Lecture in Arabic, containing no crookedness, that haply they may ward off ( evil ).<?php break;}
case 29:{?>Allah coineth a similitude : A man in relation to whom are several part owners, quarrelling, and a man belonging wholly to one man. Are the two equal in similitude? Praise be to Allah! But most of them know not.<?php break;}
case 30:{?>Lo! thou wilt die, and lo! they will die;<?php break;}
case 31:{?>Then lo! on the Day of Resurrection, before your Lord ye will dispute.<?php break;}
case 32:{?>And who doth greater wrong than he who telleth a lie against Allah, and denieth the truth when it reacheth him? Will not the home of disbelievers be in hell?<?php break;}
case 33:{?>And whoso bringeth the truth and believeth therein Such are the dutiful.<?php break;}
case 34:{?>They shall have what they will of their Lord ' s bounty. That is the reward of the good :<?php break;}
case 35:{?>That Allah will remit from them the worst of what they did, and will pay them for reward the best they used to Jo.<?php break;}
case 36:{?>Will not Allah defend His slave? Yet they would frighten thee with those beside Him. He whom Allah sendeth astray, for him there is no guide.<?php break;}
case 37:{?>And he whom Allah guideth, for him there can be no misleader. Is not Allah Mighty, Able to Requite ( the wrong )?<?php break;}
case 38:{?>And verily, if thou shouldst ask them : Who created the heavens and the earth? they will say : Allah. Say : Bethink you then of those ye worship beside Allah, if Allah willed some hurt for me, could they remove from me His hurt; or if He willed some mercy for me, could they restrain His mercy? Say : Allah is my all. In Him do ( all ) the trusting put their trust.<?php break;}
case 39:{?>Say : O my people! Act in your manner. I too am acting. Thus ye will come to know<?php break;}
case 40:{?>Who it is unto whom cometh a doom that will abase him, and on whom there falleth everlasting doom.<?php break;}
case 41:{?>Lo! We have revealed unto thee ( Muhammad ) the Scripture for mankind with truth. Then whosoever goeth right it is for his soul, and whosoever strayeth, strayeth only to its hurt. And thou art not a warder over them.<?php break;}
case 42:{?>Allah receiveth ( men ' s ) souls at the time of their death, and that ( soul ) which dieth not ( yet ) in its sleep. He keepeth that ( soul ) for which He hath ordained death and dismisseth the rest till an appointed term. Lo herein verily are portents for people who take thought.<?php break;}
case 43:{?>Or choose they intercessors other than Allah? Say : What! Even though they have power over nothing and have no intelligence?<?php break;}
case 44:{?>Say : Unto Allah belongeth all intercession. His is the Sovereignty of the heavens and the earth. And afterward unto Him ye will be brought back.<?php break;}
case 45:{?>And when Allah alone is mentioned, the hearts of those who believe not in the Hereafter are repelled, and when those ( whom they worship ) beside Him are mentioned, behold! they are glad.<?php break;}
case 46:{?>Say : O Allah! Creator of the heavens and the earth! Knower of the invisible and the visible! Thou wilt judge between Thy slaves concerning that wherein they used to differ.<?php break;}
case 47:{?>And though those who do wrong possess all that is in the earth, and therewith as much again, the verily will seek to ransom themselves therewith on the Day of Resurrection from the awful doom; and there will appear unto them, from their Lord, that wherewith they never reckoned.<?php break;}
case 48:{?>And the evils that they earned will appear unto them, and that whereat they used to scoff will surround them.<?php break;}
case 49:{?>Now when hurt toucheth a man he crieth unto Us, and afterward when We have granted him a boon from Us, he saith : Only by force of knowledge I obtained it. Nay, but it is a test. But most of them know not.<?php break;}
case 50:{?>Those before them said it, yet ( all ) that they had earned availed them not;<?php break;}
case 51:{?>But the evils that they earned smote them; and such of these as do wrong, the evils that they earn will smite them; they cannot escape.<?php break;}
case 52:{?>Know they not that Allah enlargeth providence for whom He will, and straiteneth it ( for whom He will ). Lo! herein verily are portents for people who believe.<?php break;}
case 53:{?>Say : My slaves who have been prodigal to their own hurt! Despair not of the mercy of Allah, Who forgiveth all sins. Lo! He is the Forgiving, the Merciful.<?php break;}
case 54:{?>Turn unto Him repentant, and surrender unto Him, before there come unto you the doom, when ye cannot be helped.<?php break;}
case 55:{?>And follow the better ( guidance ) of that which is revealed unto you from your Lord, before the doom cometh on you suddenly when ye know not,<?php break;}
case 56:{?>Lest any soul should say Alas, my grief that I was unmindful of Allah, and I was indeed among the scoffers!<?php break;}
case 57:{?>Or should say : if Allah had but guided me I should have been among the dutiful!<?php break;}
case 58:{?>Or should say, when it seeth the doom : Oh, that I had but a second chance that I might be among the righteous!<?php break;}
case 59:{?>( But now the answer will be ) : Nay, for My revelations came unto thee, but thou didst deny them and wast scornful and wast among the disbelievers.<?php break;}
case 60:{?>And on the Day of Resurrection thou ( Muhammad ) seest those who lied concerning Allah with their faces blackened. Is not the home of the scorners in hell?<?php break;}
case 61:{?>And Allah delivereth those who ward off ( evil ) because of their deserts. Evil toucheth them not, nor do they grieve.<?php break;}
case 62:{?>Allah is Creator of all things, and He is Guardian over all things.<?php break;}
case 63:{?>His are the keys of the heavens and the earth, and they who disbelieve the revelations of Allah such are they who are the losers.<?php break;}
case 64:{?>Say ( O Muhammad, to the disbelievers ) : Do ye bid me serve other than Allah? O ye fools!<?php break;}
case 65:{?>And verily it hath been revealed unto thee as unto those before thee ( saying ) : If thou ascribe a partner to Allah thy work will fail and thou indeed wilt be among the losers.<?php break;}
case 66:{?>Nay, but Allah must thou serve, and be among the thankful!<?php break;}
case 67:{?>And they esteem not Allah as He hath the right to be esteemed, when the whole earth is His handful on the Day of Resurrection, and the heavens are rolled in His right hand. Glorified is He and High Exalted from all that they ascribe as partner ( unto Him ).<?php break;}
case 68:{?>And the trumpet is blown, and all who are in the heavens and the earth swoon away, save him whom Allah willeth. Then it is blown a second time, and behold them standing waiting!<?php break;}
case 69:{?>And the earth shineth with the light of her Lord, and the Book is set up, and the Prophets and the witnesses are brought, and it is judged between them with truth, and they are not wronged.<?php break;}
case 70:{?>And each soul is paid in full for what it did. And He is best aware of what they do.<?php break;}
case 71:{?>And those who disbelieve are driven unto hell in troops till, when they reach it and the gates thereof are opened, and the warders thereof say unto them : Came there not unto you messenger ' s of your own, reciting unto you the revelations of your Lord and warning you of the meeting of this your Day? they say Yea, verily. But the word of doom for disbelievers is fulfilled.<?php break;}
case 72:{?>It is said ( unto them ) : Enter ye the gates of hell to dwell therein. Thus hapless is the journey ' s end of the scorners.<?php break;}
case 73:{?>And those who keep their duty to their Lord are driven unto the Garden in troops till, when they reach it, and the gates thereof are opened, and the warders thereof say unto them : Peace be unto you! Ye are good, so enter ye ( the Garden of delight ), to dwell therein;<?php break;}
case 74:{?>They say : Praise be to Allah, Who hath fulfilled His promise unto us and hath made us inherit the land, sojourning in the Garden where we will! So bounteous is the wage of workers.<?php break;}
case 75:{?>And thou ( O Muhammad ) seest the angels thronging round the Throne, hymning the praises of their Lord. And they are judged aright. And it is said : Praise be to Allah, the Lord of the Worlds!<?php break;}
}?>